    "In label ranking, it is somehow the other way around: The alternatives to be ranked are always the same, and just identified by labels without properties (as in classification learning).",
    "It is now the ranking context that changes from task to task, which is characterized in terms of properties.",
    "For example, the task might be to rank a prespecified set of wines, say, {Biferno Rosso DOC, Signature Malbec, Karia Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc}, depending on the context, which could be described by the time of the day, the type of meal, etc.",
